com.apriori.apt.testing

Annotation Type OutputFiles


  • @Target(value={})
public @interface OutputFiles
    A set of "golden" output files that are loaded from resources. These are used to verify the outputs of an annotation processor.

    This class exists separate from InputFiles solely for convenience since the only difference is the default value for location().

    See Also:
    ValidateGeneratedFiles

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String[] value
      The names of the files/resources, relative to folder().

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String folder
      The name of a folder that contains the files to load.
      StandardLocation location
      The location in the in-memory file system where the file will exist.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract String[] value
        The names of the files/resources, relative to folder().
        Returns:
        the names of the benchmark output resources

      • folder

        public abstract String folder
        The name of a folder that contains the files to load. For a given file name (the ith file in the array returned by value(), for example), the following is the path used when trying to load the file as a resource: 
         folder() + "/" + value()[i]
        Returns:
        the name of the folder that contains the resources
        Default:
        ""

      • location

        public abstract StandardLocation location
        The location in the in-memory file system where the file will exist. The folder name is not used when determining file paths in the in-memory file system. So the resulting path in the file system for a given file name (the ith file in the array returned by value(), for example) is as follows: 
         location().getName() + "/" + value()[i]
        Returns:
        the location in the file system where the resources will exist
        Default:
        javax.tools.StandardLocation.CLASS_OUTPUT
